== Potatoes ==

Adjust rack to top position and preheat oven to 425 degrees. Wash and dry produce.

Cut @potatoes{12%ounce} into ½-inch-thick wedges.

Toss potatoes on a #baking sheet{} with a large drizzle of @cooking oil{1%tablespoon}, @salt{}, and @pepper{}. Roast on top rack until browned and tender, ~{20-25%minutes}.

== Tuna Melt ==

Open and drain @tuna{5.6%ounce}, squeezing out any excess liquid. Halve, peel, and finely dice @red onion{1/2}(diced). Zest and quarter @lemon{1}.

In a #large bowl{}, combine tuna, diced onion, half the @mayonnaise{2%tablespoon}, @celery salt{1/4%tsp}, a squeeze of lemon juice, and pepper. Taste and season with @salt{} if necessary.

Place @sourdough bread{4%slice} on a clean work surface. Place @gouda cheese{2%slice} on half the bread slices. Spread with tuna mixture. Top with @Monterey Jack cheese{1/4%cup} and remaining bread slices to form sandwiches.

Heat @butter{2%tablespoon} and a drizzle of oil in a #large pan{} over medium heat. Carefully add sandwiches; cook, gently pressing with a #spatula{} or #heavy-bottomed pan{}, until cheese melts and bread is golden, ~{2-4%minutes} per side, adding @butter{1%tablespoon} when flipping.

> Lower heat if sandwiches begin to brown too quickly.

> For 4 servings, work in batches; wipe out pan between batches and add more butter and oil as needed.

Transfer to a #cutting board{}.

== Special Sauce ==

In a #small bowl{}, combine @ketchup{1} and remaining @mayonnaise{2%tablespoon}. Set aside.

== Lemon Pepper Potatoes ==

When potatoes are done, add to a second large bowl. Toss with a squeeze of lemon juice, @lemon zest{to taste}, and remaining @celery salt{3/4%tsp}. Season with @pepper{}.

== To Serve ==

Halve tuna melts on a diagonal; divide between plates. Serve with potato wedges and special sauce on the side for dipping.